Interface InjectionAwareSuppressQuickFix

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FileModifier, LocalQuickFix, QuickFix<ProblemDescriptor>, SuppressQuickFix, WriteActionAware
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBatchSuppressByNoInspectionCommentFix, PySuppressInspectionFix, SuppressAllForClassFix, SuppressByCommentFix, SuppressByGroovyCommentFix, SuppressByJavaCommentFix, SuppressFix, SuppressForClassFix, SuppressForMemberFix, SuppressLocalWithCommentFix, SuppressParameterFix, XmlSuppressableInspectionTool.SuppressAllForFile, XmlSuppressableInspectionTool.SuppressForFile, XmlSuppressableInspectionTool.SuppressTagStatic, XmlSuppressableInspectionTool.XmlSuppressFix

    public interface InjectionAwareSuppressQuickFix
extends SuppressQuickFix
    This kind of suppression fix allows to clients to specify whether the fix should be invoked on injected elements or on elements of host files.

    By default suppression fixes on injected elements are able to make suppression inside injection only. Whereas implementation of this interface will be provided for suppressing inside injection and in injection host. See InspectionProfileEntry.getBatchSuppressActions(PsiElement) for details.
